entry.content:
Minehouse 8: Before-Hallowe'en Tour
Recorded the day before the much-anticipated Hallowe'en update. As I contemplate the possibility of exploring my world a little more now biomes are to be added to the mix, I thought this was as good a time as any to review my existing home base(s). Warning: I don't have any startling megastructures, so people who don't know me may not find much to hold their interest.

entry.content:

entry.title: Building Beacon II (Minecraft)
entry.content:
Building Beacon II (Minecraft)
As I was perched on top of a stack of gravel building part of a glass sculpture called Beacon II (Water), I looked up from my block-placing and suddenly noticed the fantastic view from up there. You will see that I am using Excess and Narc0tiq's automatic self-tidying scaffolding. But I need to work on my aim when it comes to the high jump.

entry.title: Minehouse 1: The Underpool
entry.content:
Minehouse 1: The Underpool
When I started my minehouse in the middle of an island I underestimated how big a circle I was plotting out and ended up overlapping the ocean so that my original plan of having the central platform hanging over a void went out the window. So instead I have turned the shoreline in to a waterfall in to a pool under my home platform.

entry.title: Matrixcraft
entry.content:
Matrixcraft
Larking about with textures in Minecraft. I thought I would try replacing the terrain image with hexadecimal numbers to see whether I could turn it in to something resembling the code view in the Matrix films. The music is 'Revelawesome', stolen from the Homestruck the sound track to the webcomic MSPaint Adventures, at mspaintadventures.com

entry.title: TOSS sfx shot (first attempt)
entry.content:
TOSS sfx shot (first attempt)
Your chance to point and laugh at my attempts to produce an animated sfx shot using Google Sketchup 7 and Apple iMovie 09. I almost managed it, too, except that something about my green-screen clip causes it to not register properly. The wrong green? Subject too small? Too yellow? Maybe I shall work out what went wrong in future.
